{{Orphan|date=June 2017}}

'''Homāy-nāmeh'''<ref>{{cite web|last1=de Blois|first1=François|title=EPICS –|url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/epics|publisher=Encyclopaedia Iranica|accessdate=3 May 2017|language=en}}</ref> ({{lang-fa|همای‌نامه}}) is an epic poem in [[Persian language]] which relates the story of [[Homai daughter of Bahman|Homay]] daughter of [[Kay Bahman]]. [[Shahnameh]] contains a shorter version of this epic. Composed by an unknown author in 6th  century AH, Homāy-nāmeh contains 4,332 couplets and very few number of Arabic loanwords.

