{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2015}} {{Infobox restaurant | name = Level 257 | logo = Level 257.png | logo_alt = | image = | image_caption = | established = {{start date|2015}} | current-owner = [[Namco]] Entertainment | head-chef = Aaron Whitcomb<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chicagobusiness.com/article/20141216/NEWS07/141219858/the-makers-of-pac-man-bank-on-nostalgia-to-fuel-themed-eatery |title=The makers of Pac-Man bank on nostalgia to fuel themed eatery |date=16 December 2014 |accessdate=28 February 2015}}</ref> | food-type = Contemporary American | dress-code = | rating = | street-address = [[Woodfield Mall|2 Woodfield Mall]] | city = [[Schaumburg, Illinois|Schaumburg]] (village) | state = [[Illinois]] | zip = 60173 | country = United States | seating-capacity = 1,000<ref name="Daily" /> | reservations = [[OpenTable]] | other-locations = | other-information = | website = {{URL|www.level257.com|Level257.com}} }}
'''Level 257''' is a contemporary American restaurant located at [[Woodfield Mall|2 Woodfield Mall]] in [[Schaumburg, Illinois]].<ref name="Daily">{{cite web |url=http://www.dailyherald.com/article/20150223/business/150229587/ |title=Pac-Man-inspired restaurant opens at Woodfield |accessdate=27 February 2015}}</ref> The restaurant and entertainment destination is inspired by ''[[Pac-Man]]'' and the name refers to the famous [[kill screen]], which occurs when the player reaches the 256th level of the original ''Pac-Man'' game, meaning "the next level of dining and entertainment".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/pac-man-restaurant-now-open-looks-amazing/1100-6425472/ |title=Pac-Man Restaurant Now Open, Looks Amazing |accessdate=28 February 2015}}</ref><ref name="WG257" /> The restaurant celebrated its [[soft opening]] on March 2, 2015, and its [[grand opening]] in April 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.technologytell.com/gaming/143509/quality-time-level-257/ |title=Quality Time with Level 257 |date=1 March 2015 |accessdate=23 March 2015}}</ref>
== Style ==
The restaurant is owned and run by [http://www.namco.com/ NAMCO USA INC].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailyherald.com/article/20141230/news/141239840/ |title=Pac-Man-themed eatery opening soon at Woodfield |date=30 December 2014 |accessdate=28 February 2015}}</ref> It sits on 42,000 square feet which was previously used as a warehouse for a [[Sears]] department store.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.techtimes.com/articles/22576/20141219/official-pac-man-restaurant-coming-to-chicago-next-month.htm |title=Official Pac-Man Restaurant Coming To Chicago Next Month |date=19 December 2014 |accessdate=28 February 2014}}</ref> In addition, the restaurant also features sixteen boutique bowling lanes, table tennis and social sports, as well as video and board games in the Lost & Found Game Lounge.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chicagobusiness.com/article/20150120/NEWS07/150129993/pac-man-themed-restaurant-coming-to-sears-woodfield-space |title=Pac-Man-themed restaurant coming to Sears' Woodfield space |date=20 January 2015 |accessdate=28 February 2015}}</ref> The interior decor is up-scale modern urban-chic in style and includes subtle references to the video game character 257 uses for inspiration, [[Pac-Man (character)|Pac-Man]].<ref name="WG257" /> The menu also features references to well-known video game terms of the 1980s, such as "1-UP", chocolate "power pellets", and "Game Over".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://chicago.eater.com/2015/2/23/8090077/level-257-eater-inside-opening#4675498 |title=Opening Alert: Look Inside Pac-Man Creators' Cavernous Restaurant and Entertainment Complex |accessdate=28 February 2015}}</ref>
== History ==
The restaurant was first conceived as a prototype in 2013, when Namco announced that the restaurant (codenamed ''Level 256'' at the time) was being developed in partnership with a restaurateur in [[Kansas City, Missouri|Kansas City]], saying that were eyeing the Chicago area for possible locations.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.polygon.com/2013/1/3/3831270/namco-gaming-restaurant |title=Namco planning prototype upscale entertainment restaurant to expand arcade business |date=3 January 2013 |accessdate=28 February 2015}}</ref> The restaurant celebrated its soft opening on March 2, 2015.<ref name="WG257">{{cite web |url=http://wgntv.com/2015/02/25/pac-man-the-star-of-new-eatery-entertainment-complex-in-woodfield-mall/ |title=Pac-Man the star of new eatery, entertainment complex in Woodfield Mall |accessdate=28 February 2015}}</ref>
== Events ==
The restaurant celebrated the 35th anniversary of Pac-Man on Friday, May 22, 2015. They featured a live performance of "PAC-MAN Fever" by Jerry Buckner of Buckner & Garcia.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eventbrite.com/e/celebrate-the-35th-pac-mantm-birthday-bash-tickets-16508171385 |title=Celebrate the 35th PAC-MAN™ Birthday Bash |date=22 May 2015 |accessdate=26 May 2015}}</ref>
