Television broadcasting in Greece began in 1966. Nevertheless, the first TV series was aired in 1970 and was the series ''[[To Spiti me ton Foinika]]'', aired by [[YENED]].<ref name=tovima45years>{{cite web|title=45 χρόνια ελληνική τηλεόραση: Τα σίριαλ της ζωής μας|url=http://www.tovima.gr/celebrities/article/?aid=662284|publisher=tovima.gr|accessdate=22 October 2015}}</ref> The next series was ''[[O Kyrios Synigoros]]'' in the same year. The first years of television there were only [[Hellenic Broadcasting Corporation|public channels]].<ref>{{cite web|title=100 στιγμές στην ιστορία της ελληνικής τηλεόρασης|url=http://www.tovima.gr/relatedarticles/article/?aid=116540|publisher=tovima.gr|accessdate=22 October 2015}}</ref> The first channels were the channel EIR and the TED, the channel of armed forces. Few years later TED renamed to YENED and EIR became EIRT. The public channels renamed again after the coming of [[PASOK]] in the power and they became ERT1 and ERT2. Famous series of the period of public television are ''[[O Agnostos Polemos]]'', ''[[I Geitonia Mas]]'', ''[[To Louna Park (TV series)|Louna Park]]'', ''[[Christ Recrucified (TV series)|Christ Recrucified]]'', ''[[Methoriakos Stathmos]]'', ''[[oi Pantheoi]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Το ασπρόμαυρο κουτί που μας πήγε στα αστέρια|url=http://www.thetoc.gr/media/article/to-aspromauro-kouti-pou-mas-pige-sta-asteria|publisher=thetoc.gr|accessdate=22 October 2015}}</ref> In 1989, Greek television entered in a new period, the period of private television.<ref>{{cite web|title=1989, ιδιωτική τηλεόραση: Παράθυρα στον κόσμο|url=http://www.tovima.gr/society/article/?aid=248337|publisher=tovima.gr|accessdate=22 October 2015}}</ref> The first private TV channels started to broadcast in 1989. After the creation of private channels the most series were played by them. The period 1995–2009 is the best period of the Greek television and frequently characterized as the golden age of the Greek TV. Then, many series were shot with expensive productions. After 2010, the [[Greek debt crisis]] affected the Greek television and the productions decreased dramatically. On the 28th of October 2018 the channel closed down at exactly 2:10 am. Viewers were tuned in to watch the channel's last transmission, which was an episode from the 90's hit series 'Oi Aparadehtoi'.
