{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2016}} {{infobox person | name = Mabel Barrison | image = Mabel Barrison 001.jpg | imagesize = 120px | caption = | birth_name = Eva Maud Farrance | birth_date = {{Birth date|mf=yes|1882|04|21}} | birth_place = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]] | death_date = {{death date and age |mf=yes|1912|11|01|1882|04|21}} | death_place = Toronto, Ontario | othername = | occupation = Actress, Singer | yearsactive = 1890s-1910 | spouse = [[Joseph E. Howard]] | children = }} [[File:MabelBarrison1909.png|thumb|Mabel Barrison, from a 1909 publication.]] '''Mabel Barrison''' (April 21, 1882 - November 1, 1912)<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=HXcuAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA106 Mabel Barrison: The Actors' Birthday Book: First-third series. Volume #3 by Johnson Briscoe c.1909]</ref> was a Canadian born American stage actress and singer in the first decade of the 20th century. She was born "Eva Farrance" and joined a musical chorus while still in her teens. She appeared in vaudeville and on Broadway with [[Weber and Fields]] and was spotted by stage director [[Julian P. Mitchell|Julian Mitchell]] for a role in the 1903 "Babes in Toyland". "The Blue Mouse" was written by [[Clyde Fitch]] and Fitch himself selected Barrison for a role in the play. Barrison was plagued by health problems the last two years of her life.<ref>[https://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F00C14F73D5417738DDDA00A94D8415B828DF1D3 MABEL BARRISON DYING.; Actress Has Been Ill for Two years with Consumption - New York Times, October 29, 1912 (expand in PDF)]</ref> She died on November 1, 1912 in Toronto at the age of 30.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1946&dat=19121102&id=JLw0AAAAIBAJ&sjid=IQFAAAAIBAJ&pg=4176,179527 Mabel Barrison Dead, Toronto Actress Succumbs After Long Illness. - Montreal Gazette, November 1, 1912]</ref>
==Broadway plays== *''[[Florodora]]'' (1900) *''Twirly Whirly''(1902) *''Humming Birds and Onions'' (1902) *''The Stickiness of Gelatine'' (1902) *''The Big Little Princess'' (1903) *''[[Babes in Toyland (operetta)|Babes in Toyland]]'' (1903) *''Babes in Toyland'' (1905)(revival) *''The Land of Nod and The Song Birds'' (1907) *''The Flower of the Ranch'' (1908) *''The Blue Mouse'' (1908) *''Lulu's Husbands'' (1910)
